Nottingham. By kind permission of Mrs. R. Hutchin-son, garden party is now fixed for Friday, July 4. We have secured a clairvoyante palmist, and are hoping to arrange some children's dances. Tickets, 1s., include tea. Entertainments from 4 p.m. to 6.30; speeches at 6.30. Members are asked to bring their friends.
Description: Garden party with clairvoyante palmist and children's dances. Tickets 1s. including tea. Entertainments 4-6.30pm, speeches at 6.30pm.

Raw: Members' meeting to-night (Friday, 27th), at 8 p.m. prompt, at office.

Church League for Women's Suffrage July 1, reception of delegates, Hove Town Hall, 7.30 p.m. Organ recital, Mr. Herbert Ferrers. Public meeting in Hove Town Hall 8 p.m.; speakers, Rt. Rev. Bishop Powell, Rev. Lewis Donaldson, and others.
July 2, general council meeting in Y.M.C.A. Hall, morning 11 to 1, afternoon 2 to 4.30.
Evensong, Chapel Royal, Brighton, 5.30; preacher, Rev. F. M. Greene.

A social evening will be held at 49. Corn-market, on Tuesday, July 1, 8 p.m. Mice Daukes will speak. Members are urged to bring friends.
Mre. Richards has arranged to be "At Home" to members on Tuesday afternoons in July.
Whit-ington, a drawing-room meeting will be held at 20, Cheap Street, Wednesday, July 2. when Miss Graham, of Oxford, will speak on "Why I am a Suffragette."
A meeting will be held on seafront, Friday, 27th, 3 p.m., opposite Wostern Place Miss Baenda Francklyn will speak on the ethical aspect of the women's move-ment; chair, Mrs. Richmond.
Mies Macaulay will speak at a garden party (held by kind permission of Mrs. Hume) at Eversley, Durley Road, Tues-day. July 1, 4 p.m.
also at Meyrick Road, East Cliff, Wednesday, July 2, 8 p.m.
at Landseer Road, Westbourne, Thursday. July 3, 8 p.m.
Well - attended meeting held in Town Hall on Friday night , June 20, audience very sympathetic and interested . Another will be held on Thursday. June 26. in same place, at 8 p.m.
Finchley members, please note that a meeting for working women will be held at Granville Hall on Thursday, July 17, at 6 p.m.; speaker, Miss Gwen Richard.
Will all who can will take part in men's demonstration for women's enfranchisement at Trafalgar Square on Sunday, 29th, and join procession from Aldgate
Description: men's demonstration for women's enfranchisement; procession from Aldgate

Raw: Whist party held by kind invitation of Ms. Crouch, 132, Wellesley Road, on Thursday, a great success, both socially and financially.
Ilford union is join-ing in the demonstration and procession to Trafalgar Square on Sunday next, June 29. Meet Ilford Station, 2.25 p.m.
It has been decided to enter two cars at Hespital Carnival, July 12, one in Cran-brook Ward (help needed to make paper flowers), and one Clementswood Ward.
Description: Hospital Carnival. Two cars entered, one with paper flowers, one a tableau of force-feeding. Help needed for both.

Raw: Members are reminded of their duty to take part in the joint demonstra-tion in Trafalgar Square on Sunday after-noon. A banner is being made for union, which it is hoped will be ready by Sunday, and members are asked to come, if possi-ble, to follow it on the march. We are asked to assemble at 3 o'clock at Gar-diner's Corner, Whitechapel Road, and the Wimbledon Park and South Wimble-don banner will be in Section F.
Shop birthday picnic takes place on July 5, to Ash Green, two miles from Loughton. Train from Stratford Station to Loughton at 2 p.m., then walk or drive.
Description: Shop birthday picnic. Train from Stratford Station to Loughton at 2pm, then walk or drive (1s return).

Raw: the Uniterian Church on Sunday, the Rev. Mr. Thompson gave a fine ad-dress on "Mr. Phillimore's Infamous Speech and Sentence."
Members' meeting. Tuesday next, July 1. 8 p.m., at 7, Sainfoin Road.
Be sure to come on Satur-day, June 28, to hear Miss Myers and Miss Rickard.
On July 2 it is hoped Miss Margaret Wright will have a large audi-ence.
Will anyone kindly volunteer to sell papers outside Gamage's, in Holborn, on Saturday morn-ing post, June 27
and on Saturday. July 5, from 11.30 to 1.30
Will Miss Sylvia Pankhurst spoke at Hackney Baths last Thursday.
Members, please rally at these meetings. (Hon. Sec.. Mrs. I. Ives, 38, The Crescent, South Tottenham.)
Description: Members rally. Procession to Trafalgar Square.

Raw: meeting positively must be held in July , so the sooner jumbles are sent in the better for organisers of sale
Will all members please make special effort to be present at meeting at Purley on July 7 , at 8.15 , to be followed by reception and kindly promised for occasion
Description: Meeting followed by reception in a garden

Raw: Jumble sale parcels will be gratefully received for sale on July 15
Chelsea is sending a dona-tion towards expenses of great demonstra-tion in Gladstone Park on July 13. Will members please make a note of date, and arrange to walk in procession?
As local carnival takes place on Thursday next, July 3. usual weekly meet-ing will be held on Wednesday next week, instead.
Members and friends are invited to open air whist drive, to be held on Satur-day next in garden. 4. Stonard Road, Palmer's Green (tickets, 1s. each, includ-ing refreshments), 6 p.m. sharp.
Description: Open air whist drive. Tickets 1s including refreshments.

Raw: Will members please concentrate on indoor meeting for Friday next, June 27? Speaker, Miss Evelyn Sharp; chair, Miss Ethel Froud. 7.30 p.m.
Many thanks to these members who are helping to make meetings in Royal Vic-toria Rooms a succe…õe. Next meeting there will be Monday, June 30. 3 p.m.
A meeting for women only will be held that evening, at 8 p.m., in Wooleton.
